You can use a trick useing the new Viewer-API. When creating a new TreeColumn you do something like this (which is a hack though):

---------------8<---------------
TreeColumn column1 = new TreeColumn(tree,SWT.NONE);

TreeColumn column2 = new TreeColumn(tree,SWT.NONE);
TreeViewerColumn tColumn = new TreeViewerColumn(column2);
tColumn.setLabelProvider(new ColumnLabelProvider() {
    public String getText(Object element) {
        return "MySecondColumnLabel";
    }
});
---------------8<---------------

What I'm trying to say that instead of make the CNF work with I*Table interfaces it would make much more sense to make them aware of the new JFace-Viewer-API which will bring StyledText, ToolTips, better editing support, ... .
